message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Tunisia, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take around 5-7 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Public Transportation: Depending on the availability and proximity of public transportation, you can check if there are buses or minibusses that pass by or near the grocery store. This option may take a bit longer due to stops and schedules.

4. Taxi or Ride-Sharing: If you prefer a faster and more convenient option, you can take a taxi or use a ride-sharing service like Uber or Bolt. This will be the quickest way to reach the grocery store, but it may be slightly more expensive.

Consider the factors like weather, your preference, and the availability of transportation options to choose the most suitable method for your journey.
